headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had a season-high 43 points, 15 rebounds and seven assists, and the Philadelphia 76ers held off the short-handed Charlotte Hornets 127-124 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 43, 76ers hold off pesky Hornets 127-124 in OT

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Shea Gilgeous-Alexander had 30 points and 13 assists, Luguentz Dort scored 28 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied past the Detroit Pistons 114-103 Monday night in a battle of teams that entered with eight-game losing streaks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder rally, beat sliding Pistons to end 8-game skid

headlines.description: — Two-time All-Star Domantas Sabonis was ready to do whatever it took to snap a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers pull away early, hold off Wizards for 116-110 win

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks and Desmond Bane scored 21 points each, and the surging Memphis Grizzlies beat the Miami Heat 105-90 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane, Brooks lead Grizzlies to fifth straight win

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls found out they had to get by without DeMar DeRozan, then showed they have enough to keep winning, even when they're missing one of their best players.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine nets 32, Bulls overcome DeRozan's absence, top Denver

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo came back from a two-game absence and scored 27 points on his 27th birthday to help the Milwaukee Bucks defeat the Cleveland Cavaliers 112-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 27 on 27th birthday, Bucks win 112-104

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 29 points and 11 assists, Timothe Luwawu-Cabarrot scored 23 points and the short-handed Atlanta Hawks beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 121-110 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks use season-high 3s to beat Timberwolves 121-110

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Chris Paul's learned to pace himself over the years, paying attention to his 36-year-old body as he navigates the 30-35 minutes per night he usually spends on the floor for the Phoenix Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul posts 21 points, 10 assists, Suns beat Spurs 108-104

events.name: Orlando Magic at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry keeps letting it fly from any spot on the floor, and he's suddenly within striking distance of overtaking Ray Allen as the NBA's all-time leader in made 3-pointers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Wiggins lead Warriors to 126-95 victory over Magic

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Paul George had 21 points, eight rebounds and four steals, and the Los Angeles Clippers handed the shorthanded Portland Trail Blazers their third straight loss with a 102-90 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 21 as Clippers down shorthanded Blazers 102-90
